{"key":"processedPost-10708522","value":{"id":10708522,"first":10708426,"last":10708575,"when":1248105115,"utime":"07/20/09 06:51 PM","content":"If picking mature fruits is going to damage pins nearby, it's best to carefully slice the fruits off at the base of the stem or just above.&nbsp; This way, you don't damage the cake. Don't listen to those who say the leftover stumps will rot.&nbsp; They don't.&nbsp;  The pins will probably resume growing in a day or two.&nbsp; If not, pick them, and after a couple of days of 'rest', dunk the cake for the next flush.<br />RR","title":"Re: Picked ripe shrooms n pins stopped growing?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}